body:
The following prints 0, it should print 1.
```verilog
module top;
  sub sub_i();
  assign sub_i.io = 1'b1;
endmodule

module sub(inout wire logic io);
  initial begin
    $display(io); // Should print '1', but prints '0'
    $finish;
  end
endmodule
```
Internally `io` is incorrectly inferred to be constant 0 at some point. Have not investigated further.
